data.title: Saskatchewan's CanAm Scenic Highway Road Trip
data.meta_description: Saskatchewan's CanAm Scenic Highway (PR 39) highlights rural Saskatchewan. The main feature of this typical expanse of wheat country is not the natural, remarkably flat landscape, but the well-kept grain elevators that tower above the prairie. Travel through farm country to appreciate the peacefulness of wide-open spaces on this byway.
data.text:
85.1 miles: 1 hours, 20 minutes

Roll down the windows to appreciate the silence and the beauty of the vast fields around Saskatchewan's CanAm Scenic Highway (PR 39). A number of small towns, marked by their towering grain elevators, invite you to stop in for a respite, or continue to the bustling community of Moose Jaw for a wide selection of activities.

Travel through farm country to appreciate the peacefulness of wide-open spaces on this byway.
